{"title": "Quintessence of Ibsenism (Version 2)", "description": "This is an essay providing an extended analysis of the works of Norwegian playwright Henrik Ibsen and of Ibsen's critical reception in England. Shaw uses this \"exposition of Ibsenism\" to illustrate the imperfections of British society, using the idea of an imaginary \"community of a thousand persons,\" divided into three categories: Philistines, Idealists, and the lone Realist.<br /><br />\nThe main discussion revolves around Ibsen's recurring topic of the strong character holding out against social hypocrisy, while stating in his essay's final sentence that the quintessence of Ibsenism is that \"there is no formula.\" ( Michele Eaton)", "duration": 15477, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "603", "name": "George Bernard Shaw"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/quintessenceibsenism_2_1412_librivox/quintessence_of_ibsenism_version_2_1412.jpg", "copyright_year": "1891", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Literary Criticism"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Michele Eaton"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Michele Eaton"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [20], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quintessenceibsenism_2_1412_librivox/quintessenceofibsenism_00_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 248}, {"section": 1, "title": "The Two Pioneers", "readers": [9136], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quintessenceibsenism_2_1412_librivox/quintessenceofibsenism_01_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1608}, {"section": 2, "title": "Ideals and Idealists", "readers": [9593], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quintessenceibsenism_2_1412_librivox/quintessenceofibsenism_02_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1151}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Womanly Woman", "readers": [9593], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/quintessenceibsenism_2_1412